                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d191">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">390.1115A/676: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Rangoon</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schnare</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rangoon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-31T13:00:00+06:30"
                            >January 31, 1942—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 31—11:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>106. Referring to the Department’s telegram No. 51, December 20, second
                        paragraph.<note n="19" xml:id="d191fn19">See <ref
                            target="frus1941v05#pg_450">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, p. 450</ref>, footnote 71.</note> When full
                    emergency capacity of vessel within number of life preservers available not
                    needed for American citizens and their families may persons of other
                    nationalities be covered by emergency certificates?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schnare</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
